Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.8 (LSGM8080) powder, showing the highest electrical conductivity among LSGMs of various compositions, is synthesized using the glycine nitrate process (GNP) and used as the electrolyte for an intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Performance of strontium- and magnesium-doped lanthanum gallate electrolyte with lanthanum-doped ceria as a buffer layer for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The LDC (Ce0.55La0.45O1.775) powder is synthesized by a solid-state reaction and employed as the material for a buffer layer to prevent the reaction between the anode and electrolyte materials.
Titulo: Performance of strontium- and magnesium-doped lanthanum gallate electrolyte with lanthanum-doped ceria as a buffer layer for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The LDC also serves as the skeleton material for the anode.
Titulo: Performance of strontium- and magnesium-doped lanthanum gallate electrolyte with lanthanum-doped ceria as a buffer layer for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: An anode-supported single cell with an active area of 1cm(2) is constructed for performance evaluation.
Titulo: Performance of strontium- and magnesium-doped lanthanum gallate electrolyte with lanthanum-doped ceria as a buffer layer for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: A single-cell test is performed at 750 and 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance of strontium- and magnesium-doped lanthanum gallate electrolyte with lanthanum-doped ceria as a buffer layer for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the cell 459 and 664 mW cm(-2) at 750 and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Performance of strontium- and magnesium-doped lanthanum gallate electrolyte with lanthanum-doped ceria as a buffer layer for IT-SOFCs
